.TH SPACEGL_VULKAN 1 "2026-04-19" "SpaceGL @VERSION@" "SpaceGL Manual"
.SH NAME
spacegl_vulkan \- SpaceGL Vulkan 3D rendering frontend
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spacegl_vulkan
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B spacegl_vulkan
is the high-performance Vulkan-based 3D rendering frontend for the
SpaceGL engine. It uses GLFW for window management and renders all
galaxy objects (ships, torpedoes, Quantum Cores, particle effects)
using a custom Vulkan pipeline with SPIR-V compiled shaders.
.PP
Features include HDR rendering, multi-pass Bloom with Gaussian blur,
ACES Filmic Tone Mapping, compute-shader-driven particle systems, and
wireframe cloaking effects for Romulan vessels.
.PP
This binary is typically launched automatically by
.BR spacegl_client (1)
when the
.B vk
argument is specified. It can also be started independently to attach
to an existing shared memory segment.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/spacegl_vulkan
Vulkan renderer executable.
.TP
.I /usr/share/spacegl/shaders/
Compiled SPIR-V shader files.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spacegl_client (1),
.BR spacegl_3dview (1),
.BR spacegl_server (1)
